          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9IG2RbpgZuaCnrOQXjT7E_zyvbeQzKDpkEFqCpZJyndrisA4e=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I hate to do this. However, I decided this year I was always going to speak my truth no matter how much I like who or what I am speaking about. This practice is VERY thorough. They will be sure to go over all the ways to improve your oral health. Which is so important and the best I have seen from any practice. Second, I really want to support black health professionals so this is also a huge plus. Third the staff, everyone from beginning to end was so kind and explained everything so there is no confusion or misunderstanding. So here is the not great. When I have scheduled dental  appointments in the past I was always able to get a cleaning the day of my appointment that is why I schedule appts.I go every 6-8 months to the dentist and have been doing so for over 25 years. So today when I was told I needed to return to get a cleaning on a different day I was beyond displeased. This is just very inconvenient. Had I known this to be the case I would have scheduled elsewhere. I just don\u2019t appreciate the lack of transparency when scheduling. I still would recommend this practice to anyone, I would just say be sure to confirm if you can see a hygienist for a cleaning day of if you are going to a cleaning.",
